                <p> A miniature showing the moment in which Jesus is taken down from the Cross,
                  typically featuring Joseph and Nicodemus bearing His body
                  (<ref cRef="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0031.tlg001.perseus-grc1:27.59"> Matthew 27, 59</ref>
                  <ref cRef="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0031.tlg002.perseus-grc1:15.46"> Mark 15, 46</ref>
                  <ref cRef="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0031.tlg003.perseus-grc1:23.53">Luke 23, 53</ref>
                  <ref cRef="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0031.tlg004.perseus-grc1:19.38">John 19, 38</ref>),
                  and several Holy Women
                  mourning, such as Salome and the Virgin Mary,
                    (<ref cRef="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0031.tlg001.perseus-grc1:27.61"> Matthew 27, 61</ref>
                    <ref cRef="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0031.tlg002.perseus-grc1:15.47"> Mark 15, 47</ref>
